==English==

===Noun===
'''nihilation'''
# The act of nihilating

see: [[nihilate]]

===Etymology===
This word was created by w:Jean-Paul Sartre in the original french as neantir. This was translated to English as nihilate by w:Hazel E. Barnes in the 1984 version of Being and Nothingness, but was first used in English by w:Helmut Kuhn in his Encounter with Nothingness.